{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"929f4838-a62a-4f0a-95ab-c39df83c7bc3","content":"**Starting with MSTest.Sdk 3.4.0, the VSTest runner bridge is no longer included by default.** The SDK switched to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the sole runner, so `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run your tests.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 – Use `dotnet test` (recommended)\nModern `dotnet test` (SDK 8.0.400+) works directly with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Just replace:\n```\nvstest.console MyAssembly.dll  →  dotnet test\n```\n\n### Option 2 – Re-enable the VSTest bridge\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformVSTestBridge>\n```\n\nThis pulls in the compatibility adapter so `vstest.console` can still discover tests. Option 1 is the better long-term path since VSTest is being phased out.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8698641c-02f2-456c-8384-f34391a3c9cd","outputTokens":237,"requestId":"0839:5FAF2:835EA2E:926F788:69EAD84C"},"id":"8cbb6a7d-6013-42ed-8863-ec8e7918b2a5","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:41:22.784Z","parentId":"1e9eb68c-47bf-4f91-80c5-7ca472b0212f"}
